cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the problem of remote sensing image scene classification using deep learning techniques, specifically Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). This falls under the computer vision domain, which is covered by the cs.CV sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of attention maps and center loss, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, respectively. Therefore, the paper could also be categorized under cs.LG and cs.AI. Additionally, the paper involves the use of benchmark datasets, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
